The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India lose 1-4 to Uzbekistan

 - DAVIS CUP 

Namangan (Uzbekistan): Uzbekistan advanced into the second round of this seasons Davis Cup Asia/Oceania Zone Group I after Denis Istomin defeated Indias Karan Rastogi in straight sets on Sunday. 

The 20-year-old Istomin won 7-6 (7-2), 7-5, 6-1 in two hours and 33 minutes to give Uzbekistan an unassailable 3-1 lead. The hosts then made it 4-1 after Murad Inoyatov defeated Vivek Shokeen 6-3, 4-6, 7-6 (7-3). 

Istomin started the match with a break. Later he increased his advantage with another break in the seventh game. 

But Rastogi managed to pull the scores level, breaking Istomins serves in the eighth and 10th games. However, Istomin took complete charge of the tie-break to go a set up in 55 minutes. 

In the second, Rastogi grabbed the lead with a break in the seventh game but Istomin broke back twice to earn a two-set advantage after two hours on court. 

In the third, Istomin underlined his domination on the red clay courts of the Namangan Indoor Tennis Stadium, allowing his rival to take only one game. (AFP) 




